someone asked me today so here’s
to vs too:

let’s go TO the movies, it’s going TO be awesome
i was going there TOO, but the tickets were TOO expensive

to: moving toward a location or indicates a position or result
too: adverb, use for also or excessive

it’s vs its:

IT’S (it is) a shame the garden was trampled 
ITS roses were beautiful this year

it’s: a contraction of ‘it’ and ‘is’
its: possessive
i also, personally, had an issue with its and it’s the other day, so i figured i’d throw this one in too

they’re vs their vs there:

THEY’RE (they are) going to a movie
THEIR car is broken down
so i don’t know how they will get THERE

they’re: a contraction of ‘they’ and ‘are’
their: possessive
there: a place
i’ve seen too many issues with they’re/their/there lately, so i made a little cheat sheet bc we can’t keep doing this, i’m tired

addendum- this is less a decision and more of a it just started happening and i can’t really stop it sometimes so i’m really just rolling with it as best i can. it started with my friends and now is an impulse to almost everyone i’m close to, including coworkers

anyway, this is probably not a complete list, but it’s a lot of what i deal with that frustrates me the most/currently. a lot of it has to do with impulsivity

reminder- this is not a universal list and not everything on here is presented by everyone. this is just my experience

14- blurting out phrases without thinking about it. this one is self explanatory, sometimes i say things i don’t mean/don’t make sense because my brain turns off my filter from brain to mouth and i cannot process what i’m saying until i’ve already said it

13- over explanation. this is the “get to the point” i sometimes hear when i’m talking about/explaining something and sometimes i physically cannot stop myself from giving all the unnecessary info bc to me it’s important for the end information

12- unnecessary/unwanted advice. sometimes i know a thing that someone is struggling with and i will impulsively give them the advice/knowledge i have without them asking. this usually leads to tension and frustration from both parties, usually directed at me

11- special interest brain dump. this usually comes off as chatty, but i’m genuinely just excited about a thing and so i just kinda go on tangents that don’t make sense or are unnecessary for a situation and i can end up looking like i am not working/doing what i need to
10- mild dyslexia. sometimes my brain will not process the words in front of me so i end up reading it wrong and reacting in a way that doesn’t make sense to what it actually is

9.5- this is usually caused by either having lots of thought bees buzzing around my head, or bc the bees are sleeping so there is literally no thoughts in my head and i can’t focus. or i’m hyper fixated on something so it’s just like that one annoying fly that won’t go away
9- audio processing disorder. it’s where i can be trying to listen to someone but i am not processing/hearing anything they are saying so it seems like i’m not paying attention

8- hyper fixation. this usually goes along with time blindness and inattentiveness. this is pretty common- sometimes it seems like i’m avoiding doing something when really i cannot get my brain to stop thinking about that one thing, even if i’m trying really hard to

7- executive disfunction. sometimes i physically cannot bring myself to do a thing and so i end up struggling to get it done and it usually ends up late. or i don’t do it at all because i can’t bring myself to and i realize i’m not going to be able to do it before the deadline

6- dissociation. this one isn’t just inattentiveness, it’s a literal, life isn’t real idk where i am, type of thing. and bc of that i tend to struggle to do things and also sound like i’m not listening when i really am trying bc sometimes i’m aware enough to know it’s happening

5- inattentiveness to details sometimes. i’ve gotten better at this, but sometimes i can’t focus and so i’m just trying to get through the thing as fast as possible before i can’t focus at all and that means i usually miss stuff

4- time blindness. i got a watch specifically so i can pay attention to the time, but even that sometimes doesn’t help. i can think 10 minutes has passed when it’s really been 45, so at work i end up looking like i’m not working and that i’m avoiding some part of the job

3- rejection sensitive dysphoria (RSD). this one i’ve heard is pretty common where when i’m given feedback on something that is something i have to work on, i immediately blame myself and beat myself up about it, making me anxious about that thing for a long time
2- impulsive white lies. this one is usually for yes/no questions and then i have to backtrack and it makes me sound less honest/trustworthy than i am

1- impulsiveness causing me to sound mean or snappy at people. usually i’m just trying to get the information out before i forget and it’s frustrating for me bc i’m usually overwhelmed with what’s in my head so it sounds like i’m frustrated at the person i’m talking to

other note- most of these present the most at work/school so many of the examples are from those places. 
it is also a long list so don’t feel obligated to read through all of it
